HEADWORD: Circumgyration
<hw>Cir`cum*gy*ra"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of
turning, rolling, or whirling round.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A certain turbulent and irregular <qex>circumgyration</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Holland.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

